628974226364469248,Barack Obama,"It is surely the pursuit of peace that is most needed in this world so full of strife."" ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal"

name: Barack Obama
text: "As members of Congress reflect on their pending decision, I urge them to set aside political considerations.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "As Americans, we should be proud of this achievement." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Now we have before us a solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon without resorting to war." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "President Kennedy warned Americans not to see conflict as inevitable. It is time to apply such wisdom.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "I have repeatedly challenged anyone opposed to this deal to put forward a better, plausible alternative." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "When we carefully examine the arguments against this deal, none of them stand up to scrutiny.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "If Iran violates this deal, we will have ample opportunity to respond." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Worry less about being labeled weak. Worry more about getting it right.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "How can we in good conscience justify war before we have tested a diplomatic agreement that achieves our objectives?" ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúThe choice we face is ultimately between diplomacy or some sort of war.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúWalk away from this agreement and you will get a better deal‚Äîfor Iran.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúThose who say we can walk away from this deal and maintain sanctions are selling a fantasy.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "We will continue to have sanctions in place on Iran's support for terrorism and violation of human rights."‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúThere is no scenario where sanctions relief turns Iran into the region's dominate power.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúAn argument against sanctions relief is effectively an argument against any diplomatic solution.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Without this deal, the scenarios that critics warn about happening in 15 years could happen six months from now." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "The bottom line is, if Iran cheats, we can catch them‚Äîand we will." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúThis deal is not just the best choice among alternatives‚Äîthis is the strongest non-proliferation agreement ever.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúIf Iran violates the agreement over the next decade all of the sanctions can snap back in to place.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Iran has powerful incentives to keep its commitments." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "This deal shuts off the type of covert program Iran has pursued in the past.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "In July, we reached a comprehensive plan of action that meets our objectives." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "What was once proclaimed as a historic mistake is now held up as a success." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúThe progress of Iran's nuclear program was halted for the first time in a decade.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "It was diplomacy that ratcheted up the pressure on Iran." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Winning this global buy-in was not easy. I know. I was there." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "What made our new approach more effective was our ability to draw upon new U.N. Security Council resolutions." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúIt was our very willingness to negotiate that helped America rally the world to our cause.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "I have also made clear my preference for a peaceful diplomatic resolution of the issue." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Even before taking office, I made clear that Iran would not be allowed to acquire a nuclear weapon on my watch." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "The question then is not whether to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon, but how." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "Now more than ever, we need clear thinking in our foreign policy." ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: ‚ÄúMore than a decade later, we still live with the consequences of the decision to invade Iraq.‚Äù ‚ÄîPresident Obama #IranDeal

name: Barack Obama
text: "If we keep taking steps toward a more perfect union ... America will move forward. There's nothing we can't do." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We cannot ignore the problems that we have, but we can't stop running the race." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We are not perfect, but we have the capacity to be more perfect‚Äîmile after mile, step after step." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Justice and redemption go hand in hand." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Justice is living up to the common creed that I am my brother's keeper and I am my sister's keeper." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Justice is making sure that every young person knows that they are special and their lives matter." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Justice is not only the absence of oppression‚Äîit is the presence of opportunity." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Let's reward prisoners with reduced sentences if they complete programs that make them less likely to repeat an offense." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "I've asked my Attorney General to start a review of the overuse of solitary confinement in our federal prisons." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We should not tolerate conditions in prison that have no place in any civilized country." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "On Thursday, I will be the first sitting president to visit a federal prison." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We should pass a sentencing reform bill through congress this year." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "For nonviolent drug crimes, we need to lower long mandatory minimum sentences‚Äîor get rid of them entirely." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "Don't just tag them as future criminals. Reach out to them as future citizens." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We have to restore trust between our police and some of the communities where they serve." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We gotta make sure boys and girls in those communities are loved and cherished and nurtured and invested in." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "What doesn't make sense is treating entire neighborhoods as danger zones." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "We recognize that every child deserves opportunity. Not just some. Not just our own." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "One study found that for every dollar we invest in Pre-K, we save at least twice that in reduced crime." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "If we make investments early in our children, we will reduce the need to incarcerate those kids." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "I believe crime is like any other epidemic‚Äîwe need to stop it before it starts." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "For the first time in 40 years, America's crime rate and incarceration rate went down at the same time." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
text: "This is a cause that is bringing people in both houses of Congress together." ‚ÄîPresident Obama

name: Barack Obama
